      "text": "1996 ice hockey video game",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikidata"
    },
    {
      "text": "NHL 97 is an ice hockey video game by EA Sports. It was released in 1996 and was the successor to NHL 96. It is the sixth installment of the NHL series and the first to be released on both PlayStation and Sega Saturn. A Panasonic M2 version was in development and slated to be one of the launch titles for it, but never happened due to the cancellation of the system.\nThe cover of the game features goaltender John Vanbiesbrouck, who played for the Florida Panthers between 1993 and 1998. NHL 97 was the last game of the NHL series to feature a goaltender on the cover until Martin Brodeur was chosen for the cover of NHL 14.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "《NHL 97》是一款由艺电加拿大制作、EA Sports发行的体育类游戏。本游戏最初于1996年8月在Windows等平台发行。本游戏是《NHL 96》的续作。\n游戏主要是模拟冰球比赛。\n本游戏收到好评。",
      "lang": "zh",
      "source": "wikipedia_zh"
    },
    {
      "text": "NHL 97 est un jeu vidéo de hockey sur glace édité par EA Sports et sorti en 1997 sur Mega Drive, Super Nintendo et PC. John Vanbiesbrouck des Panthers de la Floride figure sur la couverture du jeu.",
      "lang": "fr",
      "source": "wikipedia_fr"
    }
  ]
